Apple’s Steve Jobs Is an ‘Innovation Pioneer,’ ZTE’s Xie Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-25T03:20:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/apple-s-steve-jobs-is-an-innovation-pioneer-zte-s-xie-says.html
 Xie Daxiong, executive vice
president at  ZTE Corp. (000063) , China’s second-largest maker of
equipment for mobile phone networks, comments on the resignation
of  Steve Jobs  as  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ’s chief executive officer. The
comments were made in an e-mailed statement today.  “Steve Jobs is undoubtedly an innovation pioneer and Apple
is a great company. We would like to show our sincere respect to
the big changes Apple and Steve has brought to the industry in
the past few years.  “Secondly, we are very thankful to Steve Job’s
contribution to the smartphone and mobile broadband industry.
With innovation spirit, ZTE will play a more active role in
communication, smart terminal and mobile broadband industry, and
build more value for consumers around the world.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Young-Sam Cho at 
 ycho2@bloomberg.net  